Android 2 Desktop

WHAT: Share URLs from your Android device to your desktop computer.

WHY: Sometimes you prefer watching or reading on the big screen rather than your Android device.

HOW: 

  1. Install the Android2Desktop app on your Android device. 
  2. Download companion desktop Python script https://github.com/pla1/Android2Desktop/blob/master/Android2Desktop/Android2Desktop.py
  3. Hack on the companion desktop Python script to customize the actions performed on the URL.
  4. Run the Android2Desktop.py script on your desktop computer.
  5. Specify your desktop IP address and the port in the Android 2 Desktop app. The default port is 12345.  
  6. On your Android device share web pages and YouTube videos to the Android 2 Desktop app. 
  
 


  